Nyamira county assembly Minority leader Fredrick Mosiori has urged Governor John Nyagarama (pictured) to explain how he will address youth affairs.Mosiori on Thursday said the governor seems to ignore youths in his tenure, especially in awarding tenders. He said the county government is aware of youths’ problems and needs to introduce policies that help them.Speaking in Nyamira county, Mosiori said it is time for youths to be considered. “The youths also have important roles to play in pushing the county’s development,” he said.  Click here for the latest political
news